qas.question: What is the name of one of the deaconries in which Cardinals come from?

answers.text: seven deacons in the Papal Household

plausible_answers.text: the seven deacons in the Papal Household and the seven deacons

qas.question: Where do Cardinal deacons not originally derive from?
Who is originally from the six deacons in the Papal Household?
Who does not supervise the Church's works in the districts of Rome?
Who did not provide all social services in Rome during the early Middle Ages?
Who is not given title to one of these seven deacons?

context: <b2_0>Cardinal deacons<b2_0/> derive originally from <b1_0>the <a0_0>seven deacons in the Papal Household<a0_0/> and <b3_0>the seven deacons<b3_0/><b1_0/> who supervised the Church's works in the districts of Rome during the early Middle Ages, when <b4_0>church administration<b4_0/> was effectively the government of Rome and provided all social services. <b5_0>Cardinal deacons<b5_0/> are given title to one of these deaconries.
